  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc0\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bc0 \u0bb5\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 : \u0b9a\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b95\u0ba8\u0baa\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bcb\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Ranil's house set on fire: One of the suspects fled abroad",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "The CID informed the court today (20) that one of the main suspects who is essential for the investigation of Ranil Wickremesinghe, who has been elected as the 8th Executive President, set fire to his house (last 9th) while he was the Prime Minister, has fled the country.",
        "Assistant Superintendent of Police Sanaka de Silva informed Fort Magistrate Dilina Kamage that the person named Ivan Perera had escaped and the authorities of Katunayake Airport had been informed about it.",
        "The trial of the case of the burning of President Ranil Wickremesinghe's house came up for hearing today in the presence of Fort Justice Dilina Gamage.",
        "During this, the 4 suspects who were arrested and remanded were also produced in the court. Three of them were present in the forum for identification parade.",
        "President's Counsel Nalinda Inradissa appeared for the suspects and Misbah Sattar, senior counsel and UNT treasurer, appeared for the rights of the aggrieved party, President Ranil Wickremesinghe.",
        "First, three of the suspects were subjected to identification parades. However, due to a power outage, the activities were halted.",
        "In this situation, President's Counsel Nalinda Inradissa, who presented the issues in the court on behalf of the suspects, said that the arrested suspects were not involved in the arson, and they had nothing to do with it, and the real criminals were walking freely.",
        "In this situation, Senior Advocate Misbah Sattar, who appeared for the rights of President Ranil Wickremesinghe, said that valuable books have been destroyed in the burnt house and it is an unforgivable crime and a disaster. Therefore, he said, there should be an independent inquiry into the matter.",
        "During this, President's lawyer Nalinda Inradissa mentioned that there is information that a person wanted by the CID has gone abroad.",
        "After this, when the judge inquired about it from the CIT, the responding Assistant Superintendent of Police Sanaka de Silva mentioned that the suspect Ivan Perera had gone abroad and he was necessary for investigation.",
        "Judge Thilinagamake, who examined the matter, adjourned the identification parade and the case till the 27th and ordered the four suspects to be remanded until then. As well as already CCRIV. He directed the CIT to quickly arrest the real culprits while obtaining court permission to obtain footage and media footage."
      ],
